{"cursor":"2745","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Roy Apps' (born 1951) is a British screenwriter, dramatist and\nchildrenâs author.\n\nRoy Apps was one of only four writers ever to have received a personal BAFTA for\noutstanding contributions to childrenâs film and television. BBC News\narticle on Children's Bafta awards 2001\nhttp://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/1688902.stm/\n\nFor 10 years he wrote for the award-winning CBBC series Byker Grove where his\nfirst job was to write out the showâs leading characters âPJ and Duncanâ played\nby Ant and Dec. He co-devised and wrote for the award-winning series ''The Ghost\nHunter'' and has contributed to many other TV series, including Chucklevision,\nBarmy Aunt Boomerang, Stacey Stone and Casper's Scare School. Roy Apps on\nIMDb http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1131840/\n\nHe has written over a hundred scripts for BBC radio, including Fungus the\nBogeyman, which won a Sony Award. His most recent work includes The Master & Mrs\nTucker, a play about the friendship between NoÃ«l Coward and E Nesbit and Life\nBegins at Crawley, a comedy drama featuring Penelope Keith. Both of these dramas\nwere made for BBC Radio 4 by the award-winning independent production company\nPier Productions.\n\nHe is the author of 66 childrenâs books, including the bestseller How to Handle\nYour Teacher. http://www.greatvine.com/roy-apps\n\nIn 1991, his novel The Secret Summer of Daniel Lyons won the Writersâ Guild\nChildrenâs Book Award and was shortlisted for the Whitbread Awards. The Fang\nGang series is published by Bloomsbury. The latest books in his sports series\n\"Dream to Win\" are to be published in Autumn 2012 by Franklin Watts.\nFranklin Watts - Dream to Win http://www.franklinwatts.co.uk/RELUCTANT-READERS_Books_EDGE-DREAM-TO-\nWIN_Series_26394_57550.htm/\n\nHe regularly visits schools to help young writers create books, plays, films,\npoetry, musical theatre and opera. He has been Writer-in-Residence at The Museum\nof Canterbury, OperaHouse Music Projects, the Aspire Trust, the Palace Theatre,\nWestcliff-on-Sea and The National Gallery, London.\n","linknr":113,"url":"Roy_Apps","recorded":1374520539,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Roy_Apps&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Roy_Apps&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources","/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability","/wiki/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources","/wiki/Defamation","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:SPS","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Roy_Apps&action=edit","/wiki/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources","/wiki/BAFTA","#cite_note-1","/wiki/CBBC","/wiki/Byker_Grove","/wiki/Ant_and_Dec","/wiki/The_Ghost_Hunter_(TV_series)","/wiki/Chucklevision","/wiki/Barmy_Aunt_Boomerang","/wiki/Casper%27s_Scare_School_(TV_series)","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Sony_Award","/wiki/No%C3%ABl_Coward","/wiki/E_Nesbit","/wiki/Penelope_Keith","#cite_note-3","/wiki/Franklin_Watts","#cite_note-4","/wiki/Aspire_Trust","/w/index.php?title=Roy_Apps&action=edit&section=1","http://www.royapps.co.uk/","/w/index.php?title=Roy_